UPDATE module_lessons SET written_steps = $__MD__$1. Before starting the vehicle, ensure all brakes are in good working condition and properly secured.
2. Familiarize yourself with the brake warning lights on your dashboard and understand their meanings.
3. Always wear gloves when handling brake components to prevent skin irritation and injury.
4. When replacing brake pads or rotors, ensure proper torque specifications are met to avoid damage to other vehicle components.
5. Verify brake fluid levels regularly and top off as needed to maintain optimal performance.
6. Regularly inspect brake hoses for signs of wear, cracks, or damage, and replace if necessary.$__MD__$, audio_script = $__MD__$Hello students, today we're going to cover the importance of brake safety. Can anyone tell me what the first thing they do when getting behind the wheel? (pause) That's right, checking the brakes. It's crucial to ensure all brakes are in good working condition before starting the vehicle. Let's move on to some scenarios where brake failure could occur.$__MD__$, practice_activities = $__MD__$[{"type": "scenario", "title": "Brake Failure Scenario", "description": "You're driving down the highway when you hear a grinding noise coming from the rear wheels. The vehicle starts to pull to one side and you feel a loss of braking power.", "questions": ["What do you do first?", "How would you diagnose the problem?"]}, {"type": "scenario", "title": "Brake Pad Replacement", "description": "You're replacing brake pads on your vehicle. You've removed the old pads and are about to install the new ones.", "questions": ["What torque specification should you use?", "How do you ensure proper alignment of the new pads?"]}]$__MD__$::jsonb, visual_diagrams = $__MD__$[{"type": "diagram", "description": "Brake Warning Lights", "labels": ["Brake Pad Wear", "Brake Fluid Low", "Wheel Bearing Failure"]}, {"type": "diagram", "description": "Brake System Components", "labels": ["Master Cylinder", "Brake Lines", "Brake Pads"]}]$__MD__$::jsonb WHERE id = 1001;
